49
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:28,080
Australia has a very vital role

50
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:31,600
as the root. Mooladhara means

51
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:36,400
the root, the root that on which everything stands.

52
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:40,120
And so as you deepen in Sahaja Yoga you'll understand

53
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,840
what vital role we have to play.

54
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:48,120
In fact India is that center which is in the sacrum bone

55
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:51,440
which is really a part of Mooladhara chakra

56
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:56,400
and it's the triangular bone in which the Kundalini sits.

57
00:03:56,640 --> 00:04:00,800
It's the center of purity, it's the center of holiness

58
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:04,960
it's the center in which the Kundalini itself resides

59
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,800
dormant and sleeping as the residual energy

60
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:12,760
which at an appropiate time in our evolution

61
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:15,480
spiritually has to rise.

62
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:19,720
So closely connected is the Mooladhara

63
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:21,920
and the Kundalini

64
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:25,280
and they are considered the first chakra.

65
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:31,400
The quality as I said, of the Kundalini is purity and holiness.

66
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:35,720
The quality of the Mooladhara chakra is innocence

67
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:39,440
and out of innocence comes wisdom

68
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,960
and with that wisdom comes obedience.

69
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,840
All of these are qualities of the Mooladhara chakra,

70
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:48,440
which we find beginning to manifest

71
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:54,600
as this Kundalini energy begins to rise and purifies these centers.

72
